<br>
Mah personal feelings in wraps are thus.. <br>
<br>
I have no doubt that there are forces or powers that be that are wanting and motivated to move our society away from any moral and or Christian 'value'. Not so much because its by some considered 'politically incorrect', but cause its not 'their bag'. There is a large and politically involved group of peeps in this nation that desire carnal freedom whom wish to remove and un-tie any and all past constraints that 'bind the flesh'.<br>
<br>
Again..these are my personal feelings in regards to many of the 'social issues' or moral arguments we find ourselves engaged in nowadays..<br>
<br>
I try very hard to remain open-minded to these arguments...to see 'both sides of the coin'. However, much of the time my personal convictions drive my attitude, disallowing me to form what some may consider an un-bias point of view....Im ok with that lol...  It is indeed a passion that we have in us.<br>
<br>
When talking about constitutional rights, and esp. freedom of religion, I try very hard not to use that as a crutch of sorts.. But I feel very passionate that it was / is indeed the moral 'fabric' of the constitution that has gotten this country where it is today. The founders of this nation were never seeking freedom from God. The freedom that they sought was that of which they felt was entitled to them by and from God...this is the moral fabric of which I speak of.<br>
<br>
NEway, no offense taken in any way. I do enjoy coming here to this message board and participating in open-minded discussions with you gentlemen.<br>
<br>
Have a great Friday everyone!<br>
