Rheaton, I have to disagree. First, for your conclusion to go through you MUST prove the existence of your god. That would be a rather difficult task, to say the least. However, even if we grant you that there is yet another problem.<br>
<br>
You are saying what <i><b>ought</b></i> to be drawn from statements you think <i><b>is</b></i> the case. However, the best that the theist can do is speculate on what is the case. Drawing conclusions of what <i>ought</i> to be done from such is folly.<br>
<br>
In order to claim that your god gives us rights you will not be able to work backwards from moral statements we humans used long before there ever was the Christian statement of God. "You ought not murder" is common sense, not divine mandate.  <p><center><font face="arial" color="CCFFFF">Lurikeen Mali'Kyre</FONT></center><center><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#150517, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='Necromancer'><font size=2 color="red" face="arial"><i>NECROMANCER</span></td></tr></table></font></i></center><center><font face=arial></center><center><I>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"</I></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urheaton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rheaton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/1/02 6:43:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Waaaaaazup!</span><hr size=1> In regards to the scripture, Matthew 6:5-6, we need to ask a couple of questions.<br>
