Rheaton:<br>
<br>
<i>"Does praying openly make one a hypocrite or is being vain in one's prayers make them hyps.? I personally do not think that Jesus was saying "if you pray in public, you are a hypocrite".</i><br>
<br>
I think Jesus was saying it is better to pray in your "room, close the door". God can see "what is done in secret". So, while praying openly doesn't make one a hypocrite, Jesus warns his followers to be seperate from the hypocrites who pray openly by praying in a private place. In short, I see Jesus saying it is better to not put prayers on display.<br>
<br>
<i>"Your a necro, you conjure up the founding fathers and ask them heheh."</i><br>
<br>
ROFL, BTW I did already. ;)<br>
