<i>"Without the belief that freedom was God's intention, freedom would merely be speculation and 'want to'. Common sense does not give us any rights to freedom making civil rights only a wish."</i><br>
<br>
I don't see that as truth. Our basic nature guarantees to us certain rights such as liberty. Where one percieves a "law giver" granting rights another sees the same law giver taking them away. Freedom is a natural state not contingent upon the laws of one or many. We are all born free (don't sing the song!) with no intention involved. Common sense tells us that such liberty is taken away. Common sense tells us that all should return to freedom. As Thomas Paine put it, "Government even in its best state is a necessary evil". Our rights are not granted by God or government but are a part of who we are as beings.<br>
<br>
<i>"The entire foundation of freedom does not stem from wanting to be free, but that we are suppose to be free. And that God created mankind to be free."</i><br>
<br>
Aside from the god part, I get the gist of what you are saying and agree. Again, we are born in a natural state of liberty. Our freedom is not granted to us by any power at all. The struggle is a return to nature. Freedom is part of who we are as individuals. <p><center><font face="arial" color="CCFFFF">Lurikeen Mali'Kyre</FONT></center><center><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#150517, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='Necromancer'><font size=2 color="red" face="arial"><i>NECROMANCER</span></td></tr></table></font></i></center><center><font face=arial></center><center><I>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"</I></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urheaton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rheaton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/1/02 12:26:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Waaaaaazup!</span><hr size=1> I find this very interesting!  This topic strikes the core distinction of Creation vs. Evolution.<br>
